Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C, fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Quarter the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2%bunch} (stalks and all). Half the @lemon{1/2}. Slice the @British streaky bacon{6%slices} into pieces roughly 1cm wide (or chop with #scissors{}).

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Pour the @water{450%ml}(for the stock) into a #jug{} and stir in the @chicken stock powder{2%cubes}. Stir to dissolve and leave to the side.

Put a large, ovenproof #saucepan{} on medium-high heat and add a glug of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Add the onion and bacon. Cook until the onion is soft and the bacon nicely browned, ~{5-7%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, just cook in a normal saucepan then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} before the risotto goes in the oven.

Add the mushrooms. Cook until browned, another ~{3-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @Arborio rice{175%g} then add the @cider vinegar{1%tbsp}, allowing it to evaporate completely before adding the stock. Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to low. Cover the pan with a #lid{} (or seal it with #foil{}). Pop on the middle shelf of your oven and bake until the rice is tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

When the risotto is ready, remove from your oven and leave it to cool for ~{5%minutes}. Meanwhile, make the salad. In a large #bowl{}, mix a squeeze of @lemon{1/2}(juiced) with the @honey{1%tbsp} and @olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} and toss to dress.

Take the lid off the risotto and stir in a knob of @?butter{1%tbsp} (if you have any) and three-quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add a little lemon juice and stir in the parsley. Taste to make sure you are happy with the seasoning - add more salt, pepper or more lemon if necessary. Serve the risotto in #bowls{} with some salad on top and a final sprinkling of cheese. Enjoy!